    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-04T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="790"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d790">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/9–453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d790fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to New
                        Delhi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-04T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 4, 1953—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191. Re Kashmir.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>UNSYG being requested by <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> hold up if
                        possible announcement <persName>Nimitz</persName> resignation for few days.
                        Report already leaked by <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>.
                            <persName>Nimitz</persName>, though refusing confirm or deny, has told
                        press UNSYG will make announcement in few days. Believed not possible defer
                        longer.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>You may indicate to <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> that while we
                        firmly believe <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> will never agree to
                        American as Plebiscite Administrator we will be willing to submit to <gloss
                            target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>, should it wish, name or names
                        distinguished Americans who might be made available for assignment.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>After announcement appears in press you authorized issue statement along
                        following lines: <list>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                            <item>
                                <persName>Nimitz</persName> has planned to resign for well over year
                                and has been induced by US Government’s request to remain on by
                                considerations of service and at great personal inconvenience to
                                himself.</item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                            <item>Most recently he again deferred his resignation so that it would
                                not affect outcome of July–August discussions between <persName
                                    corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_AM2"
                                    >Mohammed Ali</persName> on Kashmir.</item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                            <item>Clearly there is no other relationship between timing
                                    <persName>Nimitz</persName> resignation and <persName
                                    corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_AM2"
                                    >Mohammed Ali</persName> agreement.</item>
                            <label>(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                            <item>US considers resignation does not affect status Kashmir case
                                before UN and continues hope for prompt and just settlement mutually
                                acceptable to Pakistan and India.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
